  A grouping of agricultural enterprises by degree of 
provision 
with seed shows that the proportion of farms experiencing 
shortages of seed for spring grains and leguminous crops 
increased from 26 percent last year to 33 percent this year, for 
seed potatoes--from 55 to 60 percent. One out of eight farms was 
supplied with spring grain seed at the level of 60 percent of 
requirement or less. Almost half the agricultural enterprises of 
the Russian Federation were at this level with respect to 
potatoes. 


