  Monetary income in October was 18 percent higher than over 
the preceding month, and in September--by 13.6 percent. The 
absolute value of average monthly nominal wages of working 
individuals (including financial assistance and social benefits) 
varied in September 1993 in the Commonwealth states between 
14,112 rubles [R] in Armenia and R90,323 in Russia. 


